    public interface ICloneable
extends java.lang.Cloneable
    A special interface that subcedes Cloneable. Redefines the original clone method to one that:
    • Allows better type safety when dealing with cloning.
    • Hides the original clone method's CloneNotSupportedException so that it won't propagate to subclasses where no such check is needed if custom clone implementation (this interface) is provided.
    As a convenience, this interface extends the original one and thus takes the responsibility for programmers to implement it in root ancestor types.
